-- Madagascar Power Utility Reports Monthly Loss, l’Express Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-05-28T09:50:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/madagascar-power-utility-reports-monthly-loss-l-express-says.html
Jirama, Madagascar’s state-owned
electricity and water distributor, is incurring monthly losses
of 30 billion ariary ($14 million), l’Express de Madagascar
reported, citing data from the Treasury.  Enelec, which sells electricity to three towns, plans to
stop provision because of unpaid bills, the Antananarivo-based
newspaper said today, citing a statement from Enelec.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
